	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm sorry but i have to agree with the poster before you. Your cleric is your secondary so maybe you don't know this, but the high end (50+ velious cleric armor), which you WILL run for if you try his wis is all logic, is also damn near your best Ac and Sv. choices.<br><br>So stick with the +Wis folks. Verant on the highend actually kind of did right by us, for once, and made sure that the +Wis is also good for what else we need.<br><br>The only exception i might say is jewelry. I've heard (now i myself have 231 wis, and i only shot for 200, it's just i had alot of +mana, +stam, +ac stuff that ended up giving me wis too) that on the high end it's better to sacrifice your wis from jewelry for some of the high end anti magic jewelry. on that end i guess i have to agree with you, because i admit i havn't looked into it and the folks who told me it is, well a level 59 cleric to my 54 so anyone who outranks my Vicarness can tell me and i'll listen<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
